The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) will tomorrow begin the distribution of sensitive materials for the Pengana (Bassa 1) Constituency by-election in Plateau State. Daily Trust reports that the election, scheduled for August 3, followed the death of Ezekiel Afon (APC) in March hours after he won re-election to the House of Assembly for a second term. It would be recalled that INEC had already trained about 617 Presiding Officers (POs) and Assistant Presiding Officers (APOs) that would conduct the election in the constituency with 67,033 prospective voters who collected their Permanent Voter Cards (PVCs). A statement released, yesterday, by INEC Head of Voter Education and Publicity in the state, Osaretin Imahiyereobo, stated that the distribution of sensitive materials would take place at the Jos branch of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN). We’re ready for Saturday supplementary election in Rivers – INEC 67,033 to participate in Plateau by-election INEC begins movement of non-sensitive materials to LGs in Ondo Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin